abstract: >
  ArtSleuth is a computational art-analysis framework that bridges
  art-historical connoisseurship and deep learning.  It provides
  brushstroke analysis, style classification, artist attribution,
  anomaly screening, and interpretable visual explanations powered
  by self-supervised vision transformers (DINOv2) and contrastive
  vision-language models (CLIP).
